    "description": "esm-spec §9.6.4 rule 4 (RFC out-of-line-expression-templates §7.3, §9.2): the SILENT form of the pattern-opacity divergence. A high-priority (10) compound rule matches D(*(U,Q)); a low-priority (0) generic rule matches D(f). The use site hides *(U,Q) inside the target-free reference `flux_prod`, so the compound rule does NOT fire (reference boundary). The generic rule DOES fire, binding the surviving reference WHOLE via the metavariable f — a silent scheme substitution (first-order marker 1 instead of the monotone marker 999).",
